  <div id="readme" class="blob instapaper_body">
    <article class="markdown-body entry-content" itemprop="mainContentOfPage"><h2><a id="user-content-reproducible-research-peer-assessment-1" class="anchor" href="#reproducible-research-peer-assessment-1" aria-hidden="true"><span class="octicon octicon-link"></span></a>Reproducible Research: Peer Assessment 1</h2>

<h2><a id="user-content-loading-and-preprocessing-the-data" class="anchor" href="#loading-and-preprocessing-the-data" aria-hidden="true"><span class="octicon octicon-link"></span></a>Loading and preprocessing the data</h2>

<p>unzip(zipfile="activity.zip")</p>

<p>data &lt;- read.csv("activity.csv")  </p>

<h2><a id="user-content-what-is-mean-total-number-of-steps-taken-per-day" class="anchor" href="#what-is-mean-total-number-of-steps-taken-per-day" aria-hidden="true"><span class="octicon octicon-link"></span></a>What is mean total number of steps taken per day?</h2>

<p>library(ggplot2)</p>

<p>total.steps &lt;- tapply(data$steps, data$date, FUN=sum, na.rm=TRUE)</p>

<p>qplot(total.steps, binwidth=1000, xlab="total number of steps taken each day")</p>

<p>mean(total.steps, na.rm=TRUE)</p>

<p>median(total.steps, na.rm=TRUE)</p>

<h2><a id="user-content-what-is-the-average-daily-activity-pattern" class="anchor" href="#what-is-the-average-daily-activity-pattern" aria-hidden="true"><span class="octicon octicon-link"></span></a>What is the average daily activity pattern?</h2>

<p>What is the average daily activity pattern?</p>

<p>library(ggplot2)</p>

<p>averages &lt;- aggregate(x=list(steps=data$steps), by=list(interval=data$interval),
                      FUN=mean, na.rm=TRUE)</p>

<p>ggplot(data=averages, aes(x=interval, y=steps)) +
    geom_line() +
    xlab("5-minute interval") +
    ylab("average number of steps taken")</p>

<h1><a id="user-content-on-average-across-all-the-days-in-the-dataset-the-5-minute-interval-contains-the-maximum-number-of-steps" class="anchor" href="#on-average-across-all-the-days-in-the-dataset-the-5-minute-interval-contains-the-maximum-number-of-steps" aria-hidden="true"><span class="octicon octicon-link"></span></a>On average across all the days in the dataset, the 5-minute interval contains the maximum number of steps?</h1>

<p>averages[which.max(averages$steps),]</p>

<h2><a id="user-content-imputing-missing-values" class="anchor" href="#imputing-missing-values" aria-hidden="true"><span class="octicon octicon-link"></span></a>Imputing missing values</h2>

<p>missing &lt;- is.na(data$steps)</p>

<h1><a id="user-content-how-many-missing" class="anchor" href="#how-many-missing" aria-hidden="true"><span class="octicon octicon-link"></span></a>How many missing</h1>

<p>table(missing)</p>

<h1><a id="user-content-replace-each-missing-value-with-the-mean-value-of-its-5-minute-interval" class="anchor" href="#replace-each-missing-value-with-the-mean-value-of-its-5-minute-interval" aria-hidden="true"><span class="octicon octicon-link"></span></a>Replace each missing value with the mean value of its 5-minute interval</h1>

<p>fill.value &lt;- function(steps, interval) {
    filled &lt;- NA
    if (!is.na(steps))
        filled &lt;- c(steps)
    else
        filled &lt;- (averages[averages$interval==interval, "steps"])
    return(filled)
}</p>

<p>filled.data &lt;- data</p>

<p>filled.data$steps &lt;- mapply(fill.value, filled.data$steps, filled.data$interval)</p>

<p>total.steps &lt;- tapply(filled.data$steps, filled.data$date, FUN=sum)</p>

<p>qplot(total.steps, binwidth=1000, xlab="total number of steps taken each day")</p>

<p>mean(total.steps)</p>

<p>median(total.steps)</p>

<h2><a id="user-content-are-there-differences-in-activity-patterns-between-weekdays-and-weekends" class="anchor" href="#are-there-differences-in-activity-patterns-between-weekdays-and-weekends" aria-hidden="true"><span class="octicon octicon-link"></span></a>Are there differences in activity patterns between weekdays and weekends?</h2>

<p>weekday.or.weekend &lt;- function(date) {
    day &lt;- weekdays(date)
    if (day %in% c("Monday", "Tuesday", "Wednesday", "Thursday", "Friday"))
        return("weekday")
    else if (day %in% c("Saturday", "Sunday"))
        return("weekend")
    else
        stop("invalid date")
}</p>

<p>filled.data$date &lt;- as.Date(filled.data$date)</p>

<p>filled.data$day &lt;- sapply(filled.data$date, FUN=weekday.or.weekend)</p>

<p>averages &lt;- aggregate(steps ~ interval + day, data=filled.data, mean)</p>

<p>ggplot(averages, aes(interval, steps)) + geom_line() + facet_grid(day ~ .) +
    xlab("5-minute interval") + ylab("Number of steps")</p>
</article>
